^ dear professor would like to invite you ( possibly once again ) to participate in our project to improve the transparency of the reviewing process of journals in economics and psychology . 
^ according to our database , you published an article during &num in &num of the top &num economics or top &num psychology journals , namely journal of monetary economics . 
^ we are interested in how the reviewing process went for you with regard to your article . 
^ if you would like to participate in the creation of a publicly-accessible database of such feedback , please visit &website description and the short online form for recording information such as how long it took you to receive reviews , how useful they were , how helpful the editorial office was , etc. filling out &num of the feedback forms should only take a few minutes . 
^ please also forward this message to your students and colleagues ; the more input to the database , and the more it is viewed by authors ( including prospective authors ) , editors , and referees themselves , the more useful it will be . 
^ if you have questions , please contact us by replying directly to this email . 
^ &name &name & &name &name 
^ &name in the &num months since we started this project in may &num , more than &num feedback comments have been entered on our website . 
^ for a number of journals , we have reached a critical mass that makes for a useful picture of the reality of the editorial process . 
^ of course , more is better . 
^ so please consider contributing . 
